  | isbn = }}</ref><ref name="EOS1">{{cite book |editor1-first = Kimberley |editor1-last = McGrath |editor2-last=Blachford |editor2-first=Stacey | title = Gale Encyclopedia of Science Vol. 1: Aardvark-Catalyst |edition=2nd | year = 2001 | isbn = 0-7876-4370-X | publisher = Gale Group | oclc = 46337140}}</ref>。
==解剖学==
[[Image:Amoeba_(PSF).svg|thumb]]
阿米巴的细胞器和细胞质都包裹在细胞膜中，沒有固定的形状，能在全身各處伸出偽足来運動和攝食。大变形虫在运动时长220-749微米<ref name = "Amoebae on the Web">{{cite web
| title = Amoeba proteus
| work = Amoebae on the Web
| url = http://amoeba.ifmo.ru/species/amoebidae/aprot.htm
| accessdate = 2009-10-08
| archive-url = https://archive.ph/dvXvT
| archive-date = 2013-01-13
| url-status = dead
}}</ref>，在变形虫中是很大的<ref name = "McIver">{{cite web
| last = MacIver
| first = Sutherland
| title = Isolation of Amoebae
| work = The Amoebae
| url = http://www.bms.ed.ac.uk/research/others/smaciver/Protocols/AmoebaProts/isolation_of_amoebae.htm
| accessdate = 2009-10-08
| archive-date = 2009-09-30
| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090930092856/http://www.bms.ed.ac.uk/research/others/smaciver/Protocols/AmoebaProts/isolation_of_amoebae.htm
| dead-url = no
}}</ref>。它是[[异养生物|异养生物]]，通过[[吞噬作用|吞噬作用]]进食。一般是以單細胞藻類、小型單細胞動物為食物。當它碰到食物時會伸出[[偽足|偽足]]進行包圍，然后分泌消化酶将食物消化。不能消化的物質，就會通過質膜排出體外，稱排遺。變形蟲利用[[呼吸作用|呼吸作用]]得到能量，吸入的[[氧|氧]]和排出的[[二氧化碳|二氧化碳]]的工作都由[[細胞膜|細胞膜]]負責。

变形虫在显微镜下的显著特征是有一个或多个细胞核、伸縮泡及食物泡。伸縮泡作用是排除變形蟲體內過多水分，保持渗透压平衡；食物泡的功能則是储存和消化食物養分。其[[繁殖|繁殖]]方式主要藉由[[有丝分裂|有丝分裂]]和[[细胞质分裂|细胞质分裂]]，而非像一般细菌那样进行[[二分裂生殖|二分裂生殖]]。遺傳功能由[[細胞核|細胞核]]負責，如果变形虫被切成两半，则保有细胞核的一半能长成一个完整的变形虫，另一半会死去。<ref name="SC">{{cite web | url = http://www.scienceclarified.com/Al-As/Amoeba.html | publisher = Scienceclarified.com | title = Amoeba | accessdate = 2013-06-08 | archive-date = 2007-12-25 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20071225114150/http://www.scienceclarified.com/Al-As/Amoeba.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>

==繁殖==
过去认为无性生殖是变形虫的一个特性，但近来科学家发现它也能进行有性生殖<ref name=Hurst>{{cite journal |author=Hurst LD, Hamilton WD, Ladle RJ |title=Covert sex |journal=Trends Ecol. Evol. (Amst.) |volume=7 |issue=5 |pages=144–5 |pmid=21235987 |doi=10.1016/0169-5347(92)90205-P |url=http://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/0169-5347(92)90205-P |date=May 1992 |access-date=2013-06-08 |archive-date=2019-05-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190504024806/https://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/0169-5347(92)90205-P |dead-url=no }}</ref>。而且科学家发现变形虫在古代可能是有性生殖占主流，而无性生殖是近代流行起来的<ref>{{cite journal |author=Lahr DJ, Parfrey LW, Mitchell EA, Katz LA, Lara E |title=The chastity of amoebae: re-evaluating evidence for sex in amoeboid organisms |journal=Proc. Biol. Sci. |volume=278 |issue=1715 |pages=2081–90 |pmid=21429931 |pmc=3107637 |doi=10.1098/rspb.2011.0289 |url=http://rspb.royalsocietypublishing.org/cgi/pmidlookup?view=long&pmid=21429931|date=July 2011}}</ref>。
